{
  "video_id": "HDjM5lw8OYo",
  "title": "How to see past your own perspective and find truth | Michael Patrick Lynch",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12740.0,
      "end_time": 16419.0,
      "text": "So, imagine that you had your smartphone miniaturized"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 16443.0,
      "end_time": 18803.0,
      "text": "and hooked up directly to your brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 19711.0,
      "end_time": 21604.0,
      "text": "If you had this sort of brain chip,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 21628.0,
      "end_time": 24159.0,
      "text": "you&#39;d be able to upload and download to the internet"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 24183.0,
      "end_time": 25375.0,
      "text": "at the speed of thought."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 25986.0,
      "end_time": 29253.0,
      "text": "Accessing social media or Wikipedia would be a lot like --"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 29277.0,
      "end_time": 30917.0,
      "text": "well, from the inside at least --"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 30941.0,
      "end_time": 32691.0,
      "text": "like consulting your own memory."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 33247.0,
      "end_time": 36445.0,
      "text": "It would be as easy and as intimate as thinking."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 37579.0,
      "end_time": 40736.0,
      "text": "But would it make it easier for you to know what&#39;s true?"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 40760.0,
      "end_time": 43721.0,
      "text": "Just because a way of accessing information is faster"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 43745.0,
      "end_time": 45989.0,
      "text": "it doesn&#39;t mean it&#39;s more reliable, of course,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 46140.0,
      "end_time": 49245.0,
      "text": "and it doesn&#39;t mean that we would all interpret it the same way."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 49269.0,
      "end_time": 52863.0,
      "text": "And it doesn&#39;t mean that you would be any better at evaluating it."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 52887.0,
      "end_time": 54544.0,
      "text": "In fact, you might even be worse,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 54568.0,
      "end_time": 57349.0,
      "text": "because, you know, more data, less time for evaluation."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 58378.0,
      "end_time": 61773.0,
      "text": "Something like this is already happening to us right now."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 61797.0,
      "end_time": 65655.0,
      "text": "We already carry a world of information around in our pockets,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 65679.0,
      "end_time": 69908.0,
      "text": "but it seems as if the more information we share and access online,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 69932.0,
      "end_time": 72734.0,
      "text": "the more difficult it can be for us to tell the difference"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 72758.0,
      "end_time": 74875.0,
      "text": "between what&#39;s real and what&#39;s fake."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 75507.0,
      "end_time": 79445.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s as if we know more but understand less."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 80152.0,
      "end_time": 83890.0,
      "text": "Now, it&#39;s a feature of modern life, I suppose,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 83113.0,
      "end_time": 87101.0,
      "text": "that large swaths of the public live in isolated information bubbles."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 87849.0,
      "end_time": 92503.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re polarized: not just over values, but over the facts."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 92527.0,
      "end_time": 96124.0,
      "text": "One reason for that is, the data analytics that drive the internet"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 96148.0,
      "end_time": 98547.0,
      "text": "get us not just more information,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 98571.0,
      "end_time": 100757.0,
      "text": "but more of the information that we want."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 100781.0,
      "end_time": 103171.0,
      "text": "Our online life is personalized;"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 103195.0,
      "end_time": 104925.0,
      "text": "everything from the ads we read"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 104949.0,
      "end_time": 107539.0,
      "text": "to the news that comes down our Facebook feed"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 107563.0,
      "end_time": 110569.0,
      "text": "is tailored to satisfy our preferences."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 111279.0,
      "end_time": 113850.0,
      "text": "And so while we get more information,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 113109.0,
      "end_time": 116339.0,
      "text": "a lot of that information ends up reflecting ourselves"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 116363.0,
      "end_time": 118567.0,
      "text": "as much as it does reality."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 119198.0,
      "end_time": 120836.0,
      "text": "It ends up, I suppose,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 121691.0,
      "end_time": 124224.0,
      "text": "inflating our bubbles rather than bursting them."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 125331.0,
      "end_time": 127460.0,
      "text": "And so maybe it&#39;s no surprise"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 127484.0,
      "end_time": 130388.0,
      "text": "that we&#39;re in a situation, a paradoxical situation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 130413.00000000001,
      "end_time": 132544.0,
      "text": "of thinking that we know so much more,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 132568.0,
      "end_time": 135578.0,
      "text": "and yet not agreeing on what it is we know."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 137259.0,
      "end_time": 140831.0,
      "text": "So how are we going to solve this problem of knowledge polarization?"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 140855.0,
      "end_time": 145230.0,
      "text": "One obvious tactic is to try to fix our technology,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 145470.0,
      "end_time": 146956.0,
      "text": "to redesign our digital platforms,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 146980.0,
      "end_time": 150123.0,
      "text": "so as to make them less susceptible to polarization."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 150884.0,
      "end_time": 152830.0,
      "text": "And I&#39;m happy to report"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 152107.0,
      "end_time": 156747.0,
      "text": "that many smart people at Google and Facebook are working on just that."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 156771.0,
      "end_time": 158359.0,
      "text": "And these projects are vital."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 159837.0,
      "end_time": 162966.0,
      "text": "I think that fixing technology is obviously really important,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 162991.0,
      "end_time": 167613.0,
      "text": "but I don&#39;t think technology alone, fixing it, is going to solve the problem"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 167637.0,
      "end_time": 168991.0,
      "text": "of knowledge polarization."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 169150.0,
      "end_time": 172890.0,
      "text": "I don&#39;t think that because I don&#39;t think, at the end of the day,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 172114.0,
      "end_time": 173743.0,
      "text": "it is a technological problem."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 173767.0,
      "end_time": 175642.0,
      "text": "I think it&#39;s a human problem,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 175666.0,
      "end_time": 179231.0,
      "text": "having to do with how we think and what we value."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 180285.0,
      "end_time": 182900.0,
      "text": "In order to solve it, I think we&#39;re going to need help."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 182924.0,
      "end_time": 185929.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re going to need help from psychology and political science."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 185953.0,
      "end_time": 189203.0,
      "text": "But we&#39;re also going to need help, I think, from philosophy."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 190663.0,
      "end_time": 194191.0,
      "text": "Because to solve the problem of knowledge polarization,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 195522.0,
      "end_time": 197517.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re going to need to reconnect"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 198455.0,
      "end_time": 202291.0,
      "text": "with one fundamental, philosophical idea:"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 203219.0,
      "end_time": 205616.0,
      "text": "that we live in a common reality."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 206671.0,
      "end_time": 210697.0,
      "text": "The idea of a common reality is like, I suppose,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 210722.0,
      "end_time": 212285.0,
      "text": "a lot of philosophical concepts:"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 212309.0,
      "end_time": 213475.0,
      "text": "easy to state"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 213499.0,
      "end_time": 216134.0,
      "text": "but mysteriously difficult to put into practice."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 217300.0,
      "end_time": 218308.0,
      "text": "To really accept it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 218332.0,
      "end_time": 220549.0,
      "text": "I think we need to do three things,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 220573.0,
      "end_time": 222885.0,
      "text": "each of which is a challenge right now."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 224749.0,
      "end_time": 227313.0,
      "text": "First, we need to believe in truth."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 228267.0,
      "end_time": 229430.0,
      "text": "You might have noticed"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 229454.0,
      "end_time": 232469.0,
      "text": "that our culture is having something of a troubled relationship"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 232493.0,
      "end_time": 233894.0,
      "text": "with that concept right now."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 235610.0,
      "end_time": 238274.0,
      "text": "It seems as if we disagree so much that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 238298.0,
      "end_time": 241107.0,
      "text": "as one political commentator put it not long ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 241131.0,
      "end_time": 243366.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s as if there are no facts anymore."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 244986.0,
      "end_time": 249208.0,
      "text": "But that thought is actually an expression"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 249232.0,
      "end_time": 253241.0,
      "text": "of a sort of seductive line of argument that&#39;s in the air."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 253668.0,
      "end_time": 254936.0,
      "text": "It goes like this:"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 256188.0,
      "end_time": 259390.0,
      "text": "we just can&#39;t step outside of our own perspectives;"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 259630.0,
      "end_time": 261505.0,
      "text": "we can&#39;t step outside of our biases."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 261529.0,
      "end_time": 263200.0,
      "text": "Every time we try,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 263260.0,
      "end_time": 266611.0,
      "text": "we just get more information from our perspective."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 267536.0,
      "end_time": 269786.0,
      "text": "So, this line of thought goes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 271160.0,
      "end_time": 274778.0,
      "text": "we might as well admit that objective truth is an illusion,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 274802.0,
      "end_time": 275956.0,
      "text": "or it doesn&#39;t matter,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 275980.0,
      "end_time": 278126.0,
      "text": "because either we&#39;ll never know what it is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 279390.0,
      "end_time": 281181.0,
      "text": "or it doesn&#39;t exist in the first place."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 283173.0,
      "end_time": 286169.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s not a new philosophical thought --"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 286193.0,
      "end_time": 288410.0,
      "text": "skepticism about truth."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 289332.0,
      "end_time": 292212.0,
      "text": "During the end of the last century, as some of you know,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 292237.0,
      "end_time": 294531.0,
      "text": "it was very popular in certain academic circles."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 295317.0,
      "end_time": 300450.0,
      "text": "But it really goes back all the way to the Greek philosopher Protagoras,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 300474.0,
      "end_time": 301800.0,
      "text": "if not farther back."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 302252.0,
      "end_time": 304701.0,
      "text": "Protagoras said that objective truth was an illusion"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 304725.0,
      "end_time": 307632.0,
      "text": "because \"man is the measure of all things.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 307656.0,
      "end_time": 309596.0,
      "text": "Man is the measure of all things."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 310169.0,
      "end_time": 312991.0,
      "text": "That can seem like a bracing bit of realpolitik to people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 313160.0,
      "end_time": 314175.0,
      "text": "or liberating,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 314199.0,
      "end_time": 318737.0,
      "text": "because it allows each of us to discover or make our own truth."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 320618.0,
      "end_time": 324780.0,
      "text": "But actually, I think it&#39;s a bit of self-serving rationalization"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 324804.0,
      "end_time": 326671.0,
      "text": "disguised as philosophy."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 327507.0,
      "end_time": 330315.0,
      "text": "It confuses the difficulty of being certain"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 330339.0,
      "end_time": 332984.0,
      "text": "with the impossibility of truth."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 334223.0,
      "end_time": 335429.0,
      "text": "Look --"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 336768.0,
      "end_time": 339707.0,
      "text": "of course it&#39;s difficult to be certain about anything;"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 340908.0,
      "end_time": 343221.0,
      "text": "we might all be living in \"The Matrix.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 344180.0,
      "end_time": 346000.0,
      "text": "You might have a brain chip in your head"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 346240.0,
      "end_time": 347988.0,
      "text": "feeding you all the wrong information."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 349593.0,
      "end_time": 353772.0,
      "text": "But in practice, we do agree on all sorts of facts."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 353796.0,
      "end_time": 357340.0,
      "text": "We agree that bullets can kill people."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 357616.0,
      "end_time": 361998.0,
      "text": "We agree that you can&#39;t flap your arms and fly."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 362230.0,
      "end_time": 364132.0,
      "text": "We agree -- or we should --"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 365180.0,
      "end_time": 367315.0,
      "text": "that there is an external reality"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 367339.0,
      "end_time": 369420.0,
      "text": "and ignoring it can get you hurt."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 371205.0,
      "end_time": 375354.0,
      "text": "Nonetheless, skepticism about truth can be tempting,"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 375378.0,
      "end_time": 378692.0,
      "text": "because it allows us to rationalize away our own biases."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 378716.0,
      "end_time": 381703.0,
      "text": "When we do that, we&#39;re sort of like the guy in the movie"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 381727.0,
      "end_time": 384650.0,
      "text": "who knew he was living in \"The Matrix\""
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 384793.0,
      "end_time": 387518.0,
      "text": "but decided he liked it there, anyway."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 389310.0,
      "end_time": 391689.0,
      "text": "After all, getting what you want feels good."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 392271.0,
      "end_time": 394967.0,
      "text": "Being right all the time feels good."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 394991.0,
      "end_time": 397772.0,
      "text": "So, often it&#39;s easier for us"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 397797.0,
      "end_time": 401286.0,
      "text": "to wrap ourselves in our cozy information bubbles,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 402490.0,
      "end_time": 403590.0,
      "text": "live in bad faith,"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 403614.0,
      "end_time": 407364.0,
      "text": "and take those bubbles as the measure of reality."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 408595.0,
      "end_time": 414440.0,
      "text": "An example, I think, of how this bad faith gets into our action"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 414464.0,
      "end_time": 419249.0,
      "text": "is our reaction to the phenomenon of fake news."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 419874.0,
      "end_time": 422804.0,
      "text": "The fake news that spread on the internet"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 422828.0,
      "end_time": 427482.0,
      "text": "during the American presidential election of 2016"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 427506.0,
      "end_time": 430133.0,
      "text": "was designed to feed into our biases,"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 430157.0,
      "end_time": 432270.0,
      "text": "designed to inflate our bubbles."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 432295.0,
      "end_time": 434346.0,
      "text": "But what was really striking about it"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 434370.0,
      "end_time": 436984.0,
      "text": "was not just that it fooled so many people."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 437595.0,
      "end_time": 440436.0,
      "text": "What was really striking to me about fake news,"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 440460.0,
      "end_time": 441798.0,
      "text": "the phenomenon,"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 441822.0,
      "end_time": 446877.0,
      "text": "is how quickly it itself became the subject of knowledge polarization;"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 447582.0,
      "end_time": 451260.0,
      "text": "so much so, that the very term -- the very term -- \"fake news\""
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 451285.0,
      "end_time": 454689.0,
      "text": "now just means: \"news story I don&#39;t like.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 455367.0,
      "end_time": 460240.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s an example of the bad faith towards the truth that I&#39;m talking about."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 463240.0,
      "end_time": 466714.0,
      "text": "But the really, I think, dangerous thing"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 467981.0,
      "end_time": 470558.0,
      "text": "about skepticism with regard to truth"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 471476.0,
      "end_time": 473383.0,
      "text": "is that it leads to despotism."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 474350.0,
      "end_time": 477273.0,
      "text": "\"Man is the measure of all things\""
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 477297.0,
      "end_time": 481214.0,
      "text": "inevitably becomes \"The Man is the measure of all things.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 481852.0,
      "end_time": 484501.0,
      "text": "Just as \"every man for himself\""
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 484526.0,
      "end_time": 487521.0,
      "text": "always seems to turn out to be \"only the strong survive.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 488345.0,
      "end_time": 490834.0,
      "text": "At the end of Orwell&#39;s \"1984,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 492136.0,
      "end_time": 496395.0,
      "text": "the thought policeman O&#39;Brien is torturing the protagonist Winston Smith"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 496419.0,
      "end_time": 499616.0,
      "text": "into believing two plus two equals five."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 500571.0,
      "end_time": 503375.0,
      "text": "What O&#39;Brien says is the point,"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 505486.0,
      "end_time": 509907.0,
      "text": "is that he wants to convince Smith that whatever the party says is the truth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 509931.0,
      "end_time": 512816.0,
      "text": "and the truth is whatever the party says."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 513484.00000000006,
      "end_time": 517400.00000000006,
      "text": "And what O&#39;Brien knows is that once this thought is accepted,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 518385.99999999994,
      "end_time": 520939.99999999994,
      "text": "critical dissent is impossible."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 521857.0,
      "end_time": 524440.0,
      "text": "You can&#39;t speak truth to power"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 524680.0,
      "end_time": 527223.0,
      "text": "if the power speaks truth by definition."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 528880.0,
      "end_time": 533123.0,
      "text": "I said that in order to accept that we really live in a common reality,"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 533147.0,
      "end_time": 534434.0,
      "text": "we have to do three things."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 534458.0,
      "end_time": 536443.0,
      "text": "The first thing is to believe in truth."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 536467.0,
      "end_time": 538137.0,
      "text": "The second thing can be summed up"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 538161.0,
      "end_time": 543247.0,
      "text": "by the Latin phrase that Kant took as the motto for the Enlightenment:"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 543271.0,
      "end_time": 544907.0,
      "text": "\"Sapere aude,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 544932.0,
      "end_time": 546664.0,
      "text": "or \"dare to know.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 546688.0,
      "end_time": 549114.0,
      "text": "Or as Kant wants, \"to dare to know for yourself.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 550208.0,
      "end_time": 552250.0,
      "text": "I think in the early days of the internet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 552274.0,
      "end_time": 553440.0,
      "text": "a lot of us thought"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 553464.0,
      "end_time": 557274.0,
      "text": "that information technology was always going to make it easier"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 557298.0,
      "end_time": 559153.0,
      "text": "for us to know for ourselves,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 559177.0,
      "end_time": 561869.0,
      "text": "and of course in many ways, it has."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 561893.0,
      "end_time": 565731.0,
      "text": "But as the internet has become more and more a part of our lives,"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 565755.0,
      "end_time": 567714.0,
      "text": "our reliance on it, our use of it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 567738.0,
      "end_time": 570298.0,
      "text": "has become often more passive."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 570322.0,
      "end_time": 572687.0,
      "text": "Much of what we know today we Google-know."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 573299.0,
      "end_time": 576994.0,
      "text": "We download prepackaged sets of facts"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 577180.0,
      "end_time": 580830.0,
      "text": "and sort of shuffle them along the assembly line of social media."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 581357.0,
      "end_time": 582786.0,
      "text": "Now, Google-knowing is useful"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 582811.0,
      "end_time": 586700.0,
      "text": "precisely because it involves a sort of intellectual outsourcing."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 586310.0,
      "end_time": 591795.0,
      "text": "We offload our effort onto a network of others and algorithms."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 591820.0,
      "end_time": 594827.0,
      "text": "And that allows us, of course, to not clutter our minds"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 594851.0,
      "end_time": 596290.0,
      "text": "with all sorts of facts."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 596314.0,
      "end_time": 598601.0,
      "text": "We can just download them when we need them."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 598625.0,
      "end_time": 600700.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s awesome."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 601348.0,
      "end_time": 606128.0,
      "text": "But there&#39;s a difference between downloading a set of facts"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 606809.0,
      "end_time": 611635.0,
      "text": "and really understanding how or why those facts are as they are."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 613237.0,
      "end_time": 617611.0,
      "text": "Understanding why a particular disease spreads,"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 617635.0,
      "end_time": 619694.0,
      "text": "or how a mathematical proof works,"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 619718.0,
      "end_time": 621731.0,
      "text": "or why your friend is depressed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 621755.0,
      "end_time": 624220.0,
      "text": "involves more than just downloading."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 625396.0,
      "end_time": 627477.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s going to require, most likely,"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 627501.0,
      "end_time": 629603.0,
      "text": "doing some work for yourself:"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 630503.0,
      "end_time": 632343.0,
      "text": "having a little creative insight;"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 632367.0,
      "end_time": 633632.0,
      "text": "using your imagination;"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 633657.0,
      "end_time": 634975.0,
      "text": "getting out into the field;"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 634999.0,
      "end_time": 636181.0,
      "text": "doing the experiment;"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 636205.0,
      "end_time": 637476.0,
      "text": "working through the proof;"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 637500.0,
      "end_time": 638944.0,
      "text": "talking to someone."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 643533.0,
      "end_time": 647770.0,
      "text": "Now, I&#39;m not saying, of course, that we should stop Google-knowing."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 648402.0,
      "end_time": 649553.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m just saying"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 649577.0,
      "end_time": 651263.0,
      "text": "we shouldn&#39;t overvalue it, either."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 651287.0,
      "end_time": 655951.0,
      "text": "We need to find ways of encouraging forms of knowing that are more active,"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 656512.0,
      "end_time": 661560.0,
      "text": "and don&#39;t always involve passing off our effort into our bubble."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 662242.0,
      "end_time": 665583.0,
      "text": "Because the thing about Google-knowing is that too often it ends up"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 665607.0,
      "end_time": 666971.0,
      "text": "being bubble-knowing."
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 667581.0,
      "end_time": 670371.0,
      "text": "And bubble-knowing means always being right."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 671183.0,
      "end_time": 673380.0,
      "text": "But daring to know,"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 673404.0,
      "end_time": 674974.0,
      "text": "daring to understand,"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 676151.0,
      "end_time": 679217.0,
      "text": "means risking the possibility that you could be wrong."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 679921.0,
      "end_time": 682189.0,
      "text": "It means risking the possibility"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 682213.0,
      "end_time": 686540.0,
      "text": "that what you want and what&#39;s true are different things."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 688700.0,
      "end_time": 690991.0,
      "text": "Which brings me to the third thing that I think we need to do"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 691854.0,
      "end_time": 694886.0,
      "text": "if we want to accept that we live in a common reality."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 694910.0,
      "end_time": 697800.0,
      "text": "That third thing is: have a little humility."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 698510.0,
      "end_time": 700632.0,
      "text": "By humility here, I mean epistemic humility,"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 700656.0,
      "end_time": 702645.0,
      "text": "which means, in a sense,"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 703701.0,
      "end_time": 706104.0,
      "text": "knowing that you don&#39;t know it all."
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 706128.0,
      "end_time": 708181.0,
      "text": "But it also means something more than that."
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 708205.0,
      "end_time": 712655.0,
      "text": "It means seeing your worldview as open to improvement"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 712679.0,
      "end_time": 714810.0,
      "text": "by the evidence and experience of others."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 714834.0,
      "end_time": 716882.0,
      "text": "Seeing your worldview as open to improvement"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 716907.0,
      "end_time": 719300.0,
      "text": "by the evidence and experience of others."
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 720840.0,
      "end_time": 722122.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s more than just being open to change."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 722147.0,
      "end_time": 724545.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s more than just being open to self-improvement."
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 724569.0,
      "end_time": 728853.0,
      "text": "It means seeing your knowledge as capable of enhancing"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 728878.0,
      "end_time": 731404.0,
      "text": "or being enriched by what others contribute."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 732224.0,
      "end_time": 734938.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s part of what is involved"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 734962.0,
      "end_time": 737950.0,
      "text": "in recognizing there&#39;s a common reality"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 738116.0,
      "end_time": 739968.0,
      "text": "that you, too, are responsible to."
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 741633.0,
      "end_time": 743838.0,
      "text": "I don&#39;t think it&#39;s much of a stretch to say"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 743862.0,
      "end_time": 748817.0,
      "text": "that our society is not particularly great at enhancing or encouraging"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 748841.0,
      "end_time": 750560.0,
      "text": "that sort of humility."
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 750800.0,
      "end_time": 751659.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s partly because,"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 752810.0,
      "end_time": 755798.0,
      "text": "well, we tend to confuse arrogance and confidence."
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 756263.0,
      "end_time": 758704.0,
      "text": "And it&#39;s partly because, well, you know,"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 759341.0,
      "end_time": 760894.0,
      "text": "arrogance is just easier."
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 760918.0,
      "end_time": 763595.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s just easier to think of yourself as knowing it all."
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 763619.0,
      "end_time": 767316.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s just easier to think of yourself as having it all figured out."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 768513.0,
      "end_time": 771446.0,
      "text": "But that&#39;s another example of the bad faith towards the truth"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 771470.0,
      "end_time": 773800.0,
      "text": "that I&#39;ve been talking about."
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 775391.0,
      "end_time": 777627.0,
      "text": "So the concept of a common reality,"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 777652.0,
      "end_time": 780342.0,
      "text": "like a lot of philosophical concepts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 780366.0,
      "end_time": 781850.0,
      "text": "can seem so obvious,"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 782785.0,
      "end_time": 784627.0,
      "text": "that we can look right past it"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 785945.0,
      "end_time": 787929.0,
      "text": "and forget why it&#39;s important."
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 789394.0,
      "end_time": 794338.0,
      "text": "Democracies can&#39;t function if their citizens don&#39;t strive,"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 794362.0,
      "end_time": 795732.0,
      "text": "at least some of the time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 795756.0,
      "end_time": 797437.0,
      "text": "to inhabit a common space,"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 797461.0,
      "end_time": 800917.0,
      "text": "a space where they can pass ideas back and forth"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 802123.0,
      "end_time": 803909.0,
      "text": "when -- and especially when --"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 803933.0,
      "end_time": 805338.0,
      "text": "they disagree."
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 805749.0,
      "end_time": 808130.0,
      "text": "But you can&#39;t strive to inhabit that space"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 809560.0,
      "end_time": 813146.0,
      "text": "if you don&#39;t already accept that you live in the same reality."
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 815144.0,
      "end_time": 817315.0,
      "text": "To accept that, we&#39;ve got to believe in truth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 817339.0,
      "end_time": 820650.0,
      "text": "we&#39;ve got to encourage more active ways of knowing."
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 821394.0,
      "end_time": 823132.0,
      "text": "And we&#39;ve got to have the humility"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 824271.0,
      "end_time": 826978.0,
      "text": "to realize that we&#39;re not the measure of all things."
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 829490.0,
      "end_time": 832573.0,
      "text": "We may yet one day realize the vision"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 832597.0,
      "end_time": 835270.0,
      "text": "of having the internet in our brains."
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 836545.0,
      "end_time": 840464.0,
      "text": "But if we want that to be liberating and not terrifying,"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 840488.0,
      "end_time": 843250.0,
      "text": "if we want it to expand our understanding"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 843274.0,
      "end_time": 845677.0,
      "text": "and not just our passive knowing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 846585.0,
      "end_time": 850224.0,
      "text": "we need to remember that our perspectives,"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 850248.0,
      "end_time": 853399.0,
      "text": "as wondrous, as beautiful as they are,"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 854171.0,
      "end_time": 855451.0,
      "text": "are just that --"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 855475.0,
      "end_time": 857995.0,
      "text": "perspectives on one reality."
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 859960.0,
      "end_time": 860367.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 860391.0,
      "end_time": 865217.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}